  "settingsHelpTooltip": "About this setting",
  "settingsHelpShowSciNames": "When enabled, scientific names appear in grey under common names throughout the app. Useful when you want unambiguous identification or are working with field guides that use Latin names.",
  "settingsHelpGain": "Multiplies the microphone signal in the app. Use values above 1.0 only for very quiet recordings — high gain amplifies noise too and can cause clipping. Most built-in mics work best at 1.0.",
  "settingsHelpHighPassFilter": "Removes low-frequency content (wind, traffic, handling noise) before inference. Most birds vocalize above 1 kHz, so a 100–200 Hz cut-off is usually safe and improves detection in noisy conditions.",
  "settingsHelpWindowDuration": "How many seconds of audio BirdNET analyses at once. Shorter windows react faster and give finer time resolution; longer windows average more context per pass for steadier scores at the cost of slower reaction time.",
  "settingsHelpConfidenceThreshold": "Detections below this score are hidden. Lower values surface more uncertain detections (good for rare species or quiet recordings); higher values reduce false positives but may miss faint or distant birds.",
  "settingsHelpSensitivity": "Logistic sigmoid steepness applied to model logits. Higher values push uncertain scores toward extremes (more high-confidence detections plus more false positives). Leave at 1.0 unless you know what you're doing.",
  "settingsHelpInferenceRate": "How often BirdNET runs inference per second. Higher rates catch brief calls but use more battery and CPU; lower rates are gentler on the device but may miss short vocalizations.",
  "settingsHelpScorePooling": "How scores from overlapping analysis windows are combined. 'Max' is most reactive; 'average' smooths flickering; 'LME' (logit-mean-exp) is a soft maximum that balances both.",
  "settingsScorePoolingWindows": "Número de ventanas de pooling",
  "settingsHelpScorePoolingWindows": "Número de ventanas de inferencia consecutivas que contribuyen al puntaje agrupado. Valores mayores suavizan las detecciones en un horizonte temporal más largo — mejor para vocalizaciones constantes y lejanas, pero más lentos para reaccionar a llamadas breves. Valores menores son más reactivos pero más ruidosos.",
  "settingsHelpFftSize": "Resolution of the spectrogram. Larger sizes give finer frequency detail but coarser timing; smaller sizes show transient calls more sharply but blur frequencies. 1024–2048 works well for most species.",
  "settingsHelpColorMap": "Color palette used to render spectrogram intensity. Viridis and Magma are perceptually uniform; Grayscale is print-friendly and emphasizes structure over hue.",
  "settingsHelpSpectrogramDuration": "How many seconds of audio fit on screen at once. Shorter durations give more detail per call; longer durations show temporal patterns and let you compare detections.",
  "settingsHelpFrequencyRange": "Upper limit of the spectrogram's vertical axis. Reduce to focus on low-frequency vocalizations (owls, grouse) or increase to see ultrasonic calls and high-pitched insects.",
  "settingsHelpLogAmplitude": "Applies a logarithmic scale to spectrogram intensity. Makes quiet calls more visible at the cost of also showing more background noise. Helpful for distant or faint species.",
  "settingsHelpSpectrogramQuality": "Controla el filtrado de GPU usado para renderizar el espectrograma en vivo. 'Alta' se ve más nítido y se recomienda en teléfonos modernos. Baja a 'Media' o 'Baja' en dispositivos antiguos si notas caídas de fotogramas o consumo excesivo de batería.",
  "settingsHelpRecordingMode": "Whether and how audio is saved to disk. 'Full' keeps everything (large files); 'Detections only' saves short clips around each detection; 'Off' analyzes in real time without writing audio.",
  "settingsHelpRecordingFormat": "Container format for saved audio. WAV is uncompressed and universally supported; FLAC is lossless but ~50% smaller and supported by most analysis software.",
  "settingsHelpUseGps": "Use the device's GPS for live location. When off, the app uses the manual coordinates you set below — useful for stationary deployments or when GPS reception is poor indoors.",
  "settingsHelpSpeciesFilter": "Restrict detections by geographic likelihood using the on-device location model. 'Location filter' hides species below the threshold; 'Location weighting' multiplies detection scores by the location prior.",
  "settingsHelpGeoThreshold": "Minimum geographic-prior score for a species to pass the location filter. Lower values are more permissive (good for rare or migrating species); higher values stay strictly within typical ranges.",
  "settingsHelpExportFormat": "Format for exported session data. Raven is for use in Cornell Raven Pro; CSV opens in spreadsheets; JSON is easiest for programmatic processing; GPX writes the survey track and waypoints for use in mapping tools.",
  "settingsHelpIncludeAudioFiles": "When enabled, exported sessions include the saved audio files alongside the metadata table. Useful for archiving and re-analysis; results in much larger exports.",
